  "texts": [
    "Finally, we employ the Transformer model to perform global-level fusion of all learned embeddings and incorporate the structural inductive bias of the network.",
    "This fusion approach effectively and significantly enhances the utilization of all captured information, thereby greatly improving the performance of inferring the associations between diseases and lncRNAs.",
    "Our proposed model outperforms these models that exist now in terms of performance and scalability.In summary, our research makes the following key contributions:• We employ the NAFS method for feature embedding learning without the need for explicit training, and we utilize SDNE to encode the network structure.• We employ both local-level and global-level approaches for feature embedding, enabling the model to effectively uncover potential association information.",
    "• To improve the Transformer model for learning graph node information, we learn the network's structural information as an inductive bias.",
    "• We propose a Transformer fusion mechanism, which introduces the Transformer model for node embedding and fusion of multiple features and topology information, enriching the representation of lncR-NAs and diseases."
  ],
